spanGrp.span: But how was it at first?
¿Ta mẽnẽbi sögötö ra mẽnẽbi í rö
Oh yes; it looks like an otter,
¡A Jawa í rö je sũta í rö
the one sweeping the house. No.
Je dul jũ jãr sigö Kae
It was the mouse who called him.
Je nẽ ra koño koño yaba të í chagá rö
He called him and said to him,
Koño yaba të í chagá të shá ĩã
He came by, it didn’t/it picked him up.
Ñerö je damãũ je ka/ je mẽnẽũ-nẽ í yulö
He came by and said to him,
He got in and they left.
Í jẽk jiagá ñerö í mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ
They were going real fast and happy on the road.
At that point a frog appeared which was playing [with a ball].
So, in order not to kill him, he slowed down forcefully.
ñerö ka jie wã í ktö-glö-wã kueinga (_) karro je wögugá-ite derré
So they went up and the mouse flew up in the sky,
Jeska bö í wakwa kã'nãtulá-mĩ koño jũnã' siwã' inga
but he managed to hold himself on a branch.
But the driver crashed against a stone.
Ata í wagi bö (m) mẽnẽũ të jak bö tiá rö
But the driver crashed against a stone.
ñero jeska bö í juela í döá-wã kayuwö-nã í döá-wã
his spirit rouse in the air,
but they managed to grab it, and put it back in.
Ñerö jeska bö í gugá-nẽ-ite wöiarwá pakká-ite
Then the mouse called an ambulance, to get him.
ta mãga koño të ambulancia chagá pe tebeli_yaga chagá (_) í yulö-nẽ
Then the mouse called an ambulance, to get him.
Jeska í jiá-wã-ite ta ñẽ buke jiñã' jiñã' wa jebö
“Let´s take the car to the side of the road!”
But the frog did not react, as he was just crying.
Ka í mĩ ta í jñõ-gẽ bö (_)
Only the mouse took out the flat tire and took it to repair it.
Koño bö mẽnẽ-garto-mĩ koño të la/ (eh) yanta juã'-ka í bata inga Sigá-ite mẽnẽtse í wã böi-nã
Next they left, then/no, they didn’t.
Ñero tögapa í wakwa mẽnẽu-lo-mĩ-nẽ Ñerö/ no
The one I say is an otter appeared all wrapped up.
jawa sha-blá yís je desãũ-te pamõ-lë-wã-ka (_)
So the frog rushed to look for a bed for him;
Ñerö buke tunã'ũ-mĩ të jaka yulá ĩã
he lied him down, wrapped him up, and fed him;
and the next day he has cured and that made them happy;
bulilështö (_) í böi-nã'-ka-nẽ Je të í wakwa ksewẽ
so, they went to the place of the accident to look for the car, but it wasn’t there.
í mẽnẽu-lo mãĩ í ña ktá ska nẽ je sũã'-nẽ jeska nẽ karro yulö-nẽ ka í jue-nã
One said to the other “here is where you hit us”.
E-gla të í she-gẽ ĩã „jiska nẽ ba të se shká-wã rö"
At that point the fucking mouse was driving by, going up and down;
Ñerö je jueta bönẽra ñẽ koño chi damãũ nẽ karro wöksénẽ jueigweta Dá-teu-nẽ wagweta
they got in and rushed away.
Ñã jiö-ra-ká-nẽ mau-lo komĩ' jũr-gate jũr-gate
they were full because they didn’t die.’
Jeska bö í ksenã-tulá-mĩ ka í dunẽ-wã jela
